headline: Is General Dynamics Fairly Priced After Pentagon Pushes Missile Suppliers to Double Output?
summary: If you have been watching General Dynamics lately, you are not alone. With shares closing at $343.62 and notching a solid 31.7% gain year-to-date, plenty of investors are eyeing this defense giant and wondering whether the rally is just getting started or if it might be time to take some chips off the table. Over the past five years, General Dynamics has delivered a cumulative return of 164.4%, significantly outpacing broader market benchmarks. The company does not appear to be slowing down...
